  "commentary": "**SPX Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nWith SPX at 6577 trading just above the 6576 GEX flip and approaching the massive 120B gamma wall at 6580, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that resistance zone while providing strong support on any dip toward the 6575 level with 62B in positive gamma. The PIN regime dynamics combined with the wall break event and 98% 1-minute GEX surge suggests we're seeing violent mean reversion forces that should keep price action rangebound between 6575-6580 near-term. Watch for dealer selling pressure to intensify above 6580, while any break below 6575 opens up a potential flush toward the 6550 negative gamma zone where dealers flip to buying.",
